title: (G)I-DLE’s Minnie joins Wengie track
text: Minnie of girl group (G)I-DLE has collaborated with Australian YouTuber Wengie on a new track, Cube Entertainment said on Tuesday.“‘Empire,’ a new track from Wengie featuring (G)I-DLE’s Minnie will be released on Oct. 18, 4 p.m.,” the agency said.Wengie is a Chinese-Australian YouTuber and singer, with 19 million subscribers to her official channel.Minnie debuted in 2018 as a part of the six-member girl group behind the hit songs “Latata” (2018) and “Uh-Oh” (2019).(G)I-DLE are currently competing in cable channel Mnet’s K-pop program titled “Queendom,” where six female acts - (G)I-DLE, AOA, Lovelyz, Mamamoo, Oh My Girl and Park Bom - compete to be considered the queens of K-pop.By Yoon So-yeon
